            <title>[CASSANDRA-15008] NamedThreadLocalFactory unnecessarily wraps runnable into thread local deallocator </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15008</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FastThreadLocalThread already does wrapping of runnable by calling &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/blob/netty-4.1.18.Final/common/src/main/java/io/netty/util/concurrent/FastThreadLocalThread.java#L60&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;FastThreadLocalRunnable.wrap in constructor in Netty code&lt;/a&gt;. Second call is unnecessary and incurs unnecessary additional wrapping.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
